<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="T" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Third" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Third,</orth> the ordinal of three; 1) the first after the second: <bibl n="shak. son 99.10" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 99, 10</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.445" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 445</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 5.311.445" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 311</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.4.24" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. IV, 4, 24</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 5.1.2" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. V, 1, 2</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 5.1.276" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado V, 1, 276</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.1.56" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 1, 56</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.113" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 113</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 1.3.20" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. I, 3, 20</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 1.3.20" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. I, 3, 20</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mv 2.7.8" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 7, 8</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 3.1.11" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 11</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 3.1.11" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 11</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ayl 1.2.137" default="NO" valid="yes">As I, 2, 137</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 5.4.98" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 4, 98</bibl>.  <bibl n="shak. shr 1.13" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. Ind. I, 13</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 1.13" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. Ind. I, 13</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tn 1.5.141" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. I, 5, 141</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 1.5.141" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. I, 5, 141</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tn 2.3.189" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 3, 189</bibl> (<emph>let the fool make a t.;</emph> cf. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.303" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 2, 303</bibl>). <bibl n="shak. 2h6 5.40.303" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 40</bibl> <cit><quote>(the old saying is, the t. pays for all).</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 2.1.145" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. II, 1, 145</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. wt 3.2.99" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 99</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.2.207" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 2, 207</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.3.72" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B I, 3, 72</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 3.2.330" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 330</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 1.2.248" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 I, 2, 248</bibl> <emph>(Edward the T.)</emph> etc. <cit><quote>the poor t. is up,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 3.5.12" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. III, 5, 12</bibl></cit> (i. e. Lepidus, the last of the three triumvirs).<lb />2) as a fractional number, == one of three equal (parts): <cit><quote>the t. part of a minute,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.2.2" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids II, 2, 2</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a full t. part,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 5.6.78" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. V, 6, 78</bibl></cit>. Substantively: <bibl n="shak. lr 1.1.82" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 1, 82</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 1.1.82" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 1, 82</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ant 2.2.63" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. II, 2, 63</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.4.19" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. V, 4, 19</bibl>. <emph>three --s</emph> (i.e. the whole, all) <bibl n="shak. aww 2.5.32" default="NO" valid="yes">All's II, 5, 32</bibl>. In <bibl n="shak. tmp 4.3" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. IV, 3</bibl> O. Edd. <emph>I have given you here a t. of mine own life;</emph> M. Edd. <emph>thread</emph> or <emph>thrid.</emph>
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>